collectionMetadata.name: Vacant Sites Sold By URA
collectionMetadata.description:
URA acts as agent for the State in carrying out land sales for commercial, hotel and private residential developments. The objective of the land sales programme is to meet the demand for properties by the private sector, supporting the economic growth and implementing key development plans of Singapore.

The release of state land is carried out through the Government Land Sales (GLS) programme. Each programme is planned for and announced every 6 months. The GLS sites are released through two main systems - the reserve list and the confirmed list.
